| Presigned URL | A one-time-use badge that lets you into the warehouse yourself. Expires in 15 minutes. |
| Server's role | Traffic cop, not cargo truck. Directs traffic, never carries the load. |
| Chunked upload | Shipping a car in parts — if one crate is lost, re-ship only that crate |
| CDN | Mini-warehouses worldwide. Popular items pre-stocked at your nearest location. |
| Content-Defined Chunking | Cutting a book at chapter boundaries (content-based) vs every 50 pages (fixed). Edit one chapter, only that section changes. |
| Fingerprint (SHA-256) | A DNA test for files — identifies content regardless of filename |
| Hybrid sync | Friend texts you new photos (WebSocket) + you check Instagram every evening just in case (polling) |
| Signed URL security | A movie ticket with your name, seat number, and showtime. Expired? Can't get in. Wrong name? Can't get in. |
| Download resumability | HTTP Range requests = "I already have pages 1-500, just send me 501 onwards" |

